<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-04-05T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-04-05T19:00:00-05:00" n="446" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221/326: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-05T19:00:00-05:00">April 5, 1937—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>160. Your 446,<note n="57a" xml:id="d446fn57a"><hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> arrest volunteers. Advise Consul George
                            obtain and forward Department names and passport data of each and names
                                <pb facs="0515" n="503" xml:id="pg_503"/> and addresses of persons
                            who will pay for maintenance and return passage to United States. Consul
                            should understand and make clear to all the authorities concerned that
                            these persons were proceeding to Spain in violation of this Government’s
                            stipulations. Cable briefly report.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>